               <head>Makhzan-i Afghani</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>Tārīkh-i Khān Jahānī va makhzan-i Afghānī by Niʿmat Allāh, active
                     1613-1630</summary>
                  <msItem
                     class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2005005467 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85001521 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008114816"
                     n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3772-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied"
                           key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657181.0x000001 viaf_35539655">Niʿmat Allāh,
                           active 1613-1630</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied"
                           key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657181.0x000001 viaf_35539655">خواجه نعمت الله
                           بن خواجه حبيب الله هروی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21836">Tārīkh-i Khān Jahānī va
                        makhzan-i Afghānī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21836">تٲريخ خان جهانى و مخزن افغانى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>History of Afghan tribes, with special reference to the Lodi Sultanate
                           in India, written for <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc"
                              key="viaf_29062577" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/nb2007027524" role="pat"
                              >Pīrā Khān Khān Jahān Lūdī</persName>, a close companion the Mughal
                           Emperor Jahāngīr who was later executed by Shāh Jahān. </p>
                        <p>Illuminated heading (f. 1v). </p>
                        <p>Oval seal of undeciphered former author (f. 1v). </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
